The Career Potential  Ortho Clinical Diagnostics is committed to improving and saving lives with diagnostics. To do this we hire people who share this dream and are ready for new adventures. As a valued team member, you will carve your own career path and be part of building this company stronger and better than ever before. There is no limit to the experiences, opportunities and new directions you will have access to here at Ortho Clinical Diagnostics. More importantly, you will be driving the surge of a whole new direction in important medicine. That’s something we can all take pride in as we take this journey together.    Ortho is known in the industry as a leader in customer service and support. Deeply understanding and exceeding the needs of our clinical lab, hospital and blood bank customers is what we do. It’s who we are. If you join Ortho, no matter what your role, you will be expected to keep that Customer Excellence focus in your work.  The Opportunity    As the company continues to grow, we are seeking a Data Analyst (Transportation). Within our North America Supply Chain department, this position would be responsible for providing analytical, audit, and project capabilities for domestic transportation within both North America and International transportation for intercompany transactions to other locations outside the US. This position can be located in both Rochester, NY or Raritan, NJ.    The Responsibilities      Analyze departmental reports and tools and combine industry information and direct feedback from managers/carriers to identify opportunities to increase service, velocity and cost savings while also ensuring defects and root causes are identified so that corrective actions can be implemented in a timely manner within the transportation network.        Serve as the primary miner, accumulator, and presenter of data to support projects assigned to the Supply Chain group including RFQs for transportation with suppliers working closely with Sourcing, Global Enable, and Global Supply Chain (all regions).        Develop Carrier performance monitoring and reporting with dashboards developed to track performance. Assist in financial analysis of business drivers in monthly reviews, while also assisting to develop budgets and track actions to meet or beat budgets.        Drive and follow through with carrier claim process.        Demonstrates leadership for both tactical and strategic initiatives across all transportation modes and lanes.        Support assigned projects by mining, sorting, cleansing, and organizing data that presents the business case requested and provide insights and recommendations for key executive reviews.        Lead and drive action items, root cause analysis and improvements across multiple functional teams.        Employ the use of quality and lean thinking tools to identify and drive improvement opportunities.      The Individual      4-year bachelor’s degree in Business or Mathematics.        Major/minoring in Transportation, Logistics, or Supply Chain (preferred).        One to three years relevant experience in transportation analytics (preferred).        Experience in working with all modes of transportation, including small package, international freight, cold chain, and LTL/FTL (preferred).        Excellent analytical, interpersonal, financial acumen and organizational skills.        Advanced competency in database tools including, but not limited to, Microsoft Excel (Pivot Tables, Formulas, VLOOKUP functions, etc.), Access and PowerPoint.        Highly motivated, intellectual curiosity, strong leadership skills to drive actions and accountability across multiple functions teams and external partners.        Experience in working with global partners (preferred).        Adaptable to work well in a dynamic and fast-paced environment.        Ability to identify problems and implement proactive problem solving to help achieve goals.        Effective written and oral communication skills including experience in communicating upwards.        Experience working with SAP (preferred).      EOE/AA Disability/Veteran

Front is a hub for customer communication that allows companies to offer tailor-made service at scale. Front looks and feels like your email inbox with a few very important differences: teammates collaborate in the same place where external messages are sent and received, and behind the scenes, robust workflows and integrations power the efficiency and insights typically found in a CRM. More than 6,500 businesses use Front to work together to send out the best replies faster, keep messages organized across channels, and always maintain a personal touch. The result is premier, personalized service that scales with your business — and a team that works together as one.   With $138M in funding, Front is backed by Sequoia Capital, and other leading venture capital firms, as well as independent investors including top executives of Atlassian, Okta, Qualtrics, and Zoom. Front was recently named to Forbes Best Startup Employers 2022 List, Inc. Magazine's 2022 Best Workplaces list, and Y Combinator's list of Top Companies in 2022. We have also been recognized on Wealthfront’s Career-Launching Companies in 2021.   We’re looking for an outstanding Data Analyst to join our growing Core Data Analytics team. As a Core Data Analyst on the centralized data team, you will partner closely with stakeholders across Front, including Business Operations, Finance and People, to help Front make data-driven decisions across cross-functional initiatives. Additionally, you will support the growth and scale of our data team by improving the design and structure of our data mart and warehouse set-up.  What will you be doing? Support data-driven decision making across cross-functional initiatives in partnership with Business Operations, Finance, HR stakeholders Identify insights and make actionable recommendations through exploratory analysis across all parts of our data, including customer, user, financial and internal people data Develop and monitor key metrics measuring the overall health of our business Support internal data automation and enablement efforts in partnership with the data engineering team by improving the usability of our data mart and warehouse set-up Build internal tools that support the analytical needs of functional data analystsWhat skills & experience do you need? 2-4 years of experience in analytics, conducting quantitative analysis on large datasets, or an equivalent analytical role Bachelor's degree or equivalent in a quantitative field (e.g. Economics, Statistics, Computer Science, Mathematics, etc.) Proficiency using SQL to query large data sets Strong understanding of statistics and A/B testing Familiarity with Python strongly preferred Front provides equal employment opportunities (EEO) to all employees and applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, age or disability.

As a Data Analyst on the Business Operations team, you will own the data that informs the operational decision making at Anduril. In this role, you will partner with leadership and teams from across the business — from our Tower and Drone teams to our field operations team to our customer success team — to unpack ambiguous problems and build lasting, scalable analytics solutions. Your work will vary from quick-turn analytical problem solving to process and data improvements and building core dashboards and tables — all in the pursuit of helping grow how Anduril operates and measures itself.  What you’ll do: Support the Business Operations team by owning end-to-end analyses to answer some of the most important questions facing the business. For example, you will: Own the development of data pipelines through to the creation of new dashboards to help the business manage its different business and product lines Support the development of an asset tracking system so Anduril can more effectively manage and monitor it’s core products Partner with our Supply Chain Analyst to develop forecast models to predict hardware failures to help our planning and operations teams effectively manage inventory Serve as the go-to expert for the operations teams on issues relating to data integrity and data availability, including owning the testing and monitoring of the data in the Data Warehouse to ensure data accuracy Help create novel internal data apps that enable stakeholders to use the data in our data warehouse in ways that go beyond what a simple BI tool can do Create Anduril’s first data dictionary to make the current data easily searchable for all users across the company Partner with our Data Engineering team to create new data pipelines to integrate data that comes from our products Proactively identify operational pain points and inefficiencies with cross-functional partners and develop new tools and automated process to solve themQualifications: You are technically proficient: You have 3+ years as an either a business analyst, data analyst, or data scientist and are fluent in SQL (we use dbt!) You have have experience developing data pipelines using dbt, Airflow, or Fivetran and have learned some best practices along the way for working in a Data Warehouse environment like Redshift, Snowflake, or BigQuery You’ve had a hand in developing a company’s data architecture at a high-growth startup in a way that’s built to last You like to build and enjoy iterating on things quickly. You have a strong bias for action and like to work with high autonomy You are intellectually tenacious and take pride in your work Intellectual tenacity means not being satisfied with the status quo Taking pride in your work means producing something that — if you were the consumer — you’d enthusiastically use You lean into acknowledging your weaknesses and take the idea of feedback and growth seriously You get energy from being a thought partner for others and it excites you to spend time translating operational problems into data problems, and to then going and executing on them   Anduril is an equal-opportunity employer, and we encourage candidates from all backgrounds to apply. If you are someone passionate to work on problems that matter, we’d love to hear from you!

At Glowforge, we help people bring home the future and make it their own. Our printer uses a laser to carve and engrave products from raw materials like wood, leather, acrylic – even cardboard. Take a look and see for yourself. We build magical products to delight our customers, and we do it while taking care of each other. We hire people who are outstanding at what they do, who thrive in tight-knit teams, and who want to make things that make a difference. Together, we've built a product we're incredibly proud of, and the reward has been incredible growth. We work together because we believe in the power of creativity. We believe we can bring about a future where anyone can print anything. We'd love to have you join us. We're a remote-first company - just let us know where you prefer to work from! Why we need you The magic of printing things on the Glowforge is an experience we want everyone to know! And we think that magical feeling should begin the moment a visitor lands on our website. We know you’d agree! You’re a web analytics wizard who can peer into mountains of data to see your customer’s happiest paths, dead ends, short cuts and back tracks. You could work your sorcery anywhere, but we think you’ll be happiest here creating a world where everyone can turn their ideas into reality with the press of a button. Here’s what you’ll be doing As the Data Analyst for Site Experience, you’ll work closely with both the Marketing and Product teams to understand user behavior across channels, marketing programs, and audiences. You’ll define the metrics needed to answer key business questions, configure our analytics platform to track them, then report back with insights that change the way we think and operate. More specifically, you’ll:Serve as the internal authority on our user behavior and engagement across Glowforge Growth and Sales properties.Dive deep into site data to identify trends, behaviors and opportunities to use in improving site performance and customer experience.Surface testing recommendations and work with stakeholders to develop hypotheses and prioritize testing.Own implementation and maintenance of tag management and web tracking.You need these qualifications3+ Years experience in conversion optimization, product development or digital analytics.Excellent analytics capabilitiesExpertise with web analytics and digital experience platforms such as Google Analytics, Adobe, Full Story, Hot Jar, and moreWorking understanding of web coding (HTML, CSS, DOM)Proficiency in JavaScriptProficiency with SQLIt would be nice if…You have experience with CRM and CDP platforms.You have experience with Big QueryYou are personally passionate for what we’re building - and can’t wait to get a Glowforge of your own.Equal opportunity employment There's one more, very important thing. We are an equal opportunity employer. We search for amazing people of diverse backgrounds, experiences, abilities, and perspectives. We take care of each other to create an inclusive work environment where we love to come to work every day. We'd be happy to provide reasonable accommodations to help you apply - just email us at jobs@glowforge.com. We hope you can join us.

Company Description KIPP KIPP Public Schools is a network of 270 public charter schools with nearly 10,000 educators and more than 160,000 students and alumni. You can learn more at www.kipp.org. KIPP JACKSONVILLE PUBLIC SCHOOLS KIPP Jacksonville Public Schools is part of the KIPP national network. Together with families and communities, we create joyful, academically excellent schools that prepare students with the skills and confidence to pursue the paths they choose – college, career, and beyond – so they can lead fulfilling lives and build a more just world.  High quality teaching in our classrooms is not only about getting great academic results; it must also be about encouraging and equipping our students to use their voices to call out injustice and to build a more just world. We are more committed than ever to making sure ALL decisions that affect students at KIPP Jacksonville are filtered through a lens of equity and racial justice.  In the 2022-23 school year, the KIPP Jacksonville region will be comprised of four schools educating 2,000+ students, kindergarten through tenth grade, in the North and Westsides of Jacksonville, Florida: KIPP Impact Academy: Kindergarten - 2nd, 6th – 8th grade KIPP VOICE Academy: Kindergarten – 7th grade KIPP Bessie Coleman Academy: Kindergarten – 8th grade KIPP Bold City High School: 9th - 10th grade To support these schools, we will employ approximately almost 300 full-time staff members. We seek educators and colleagues that represent our core values of high expectations, growth mindset, commitment to team, trust, joy, and sustainability. To learn more about what it is like to work and teach at KIPP Jacksonville Public Schools, please visit www.kippjax.org/teach. To see all openings, visit our Regional Job Board. Job Description The Data Analyst (DA) supports the processes and tools that empower regional analysis of key performance indicators (tracking, collection, storage, and analysis of data).  The DA will primarily maintain and expand the region’s data infrastructure to support operational decision-making with robust analytics tools. This includes managing the regional data warehouse and the pipelines that move data between systems. In addition, the DA provides robust data analysis by building dashboards, generating cyclical and ad-hoc reports, and maintaining a user-friendly central access point.  The ideal candidate for this position will have a deep passion for racial justice and equity for all children and thrive on helping people. This means that a candidate understands that every data point is a child, and they keep a lens on mitigating bias and stereotypes. Additionally, the candidate is comfortable spending long periods of time working independently and in front of the computer screen but can be called upon to effectively present data to a variety of audiences.  The role is a full-time, manager-level role that reports to the Regional Director of Operations on the shared services team and is part of the larger operations team that supports schools. As a member of the shared services team, this individual would be responsible for doing whatever it takes to ensure that students develop the knowledge, skills, and character strengths they need to succeed throughout their education and in the competitive world beyond. This position is year-round and performs duties as assigned by their manager. Typical hours are 8:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m. but can vary based on role and season. KEY RESPONSIBILITIES Infrastructure Management Maintain and troubleshoot the integrity of data linkages between data source systems and data warehouse Develop and maintain documentation such as a data dictionary that describes the contents, formats, and structure of the data warehouse and the relationship between its elements Perform maintenance and support tasks on the central reporting platform, Racetrack, hosted on Google Sites. Identify, design, and implement internal process improvements: automating manual processes, optimizing data delivery, re-designing infrastructure for greater scalability, etc. Partner with regional and school operations staff to conduct data quality audits to ensure accurate and complete data is warehoused through student information and other data systems Maintain an in-depth knowledge of all regionally standardized data sources and systems, being constantly aware of new updates and incorporating changes into analytical approaches and data visualizations Seek feedback from teammates and end-users to improve the product Data Analysis Collaborate with the Data & Assessment Systems Manager to define regional data analysis and reporting plan and deliverables, school-facing data support, academic data and norms on data practices Conduct descriptive analysis on outputs from KIPP Jacksonville’s student information system, student assessments, teacher evaluations, and other organizational data platforms Design, implement and monitor the use of real-time data reports and Tableau dashboards to support strategic decisions at the regional and school level Develop predictive and statistical models with student data to support the academics, operations, and student support teams in allocating resources efficiently and making informed programmatic decisions Translate data into relevant insights and implications and support stakeholders in interpreting findings Regularly monitor key metrics and report significant changes or trends Data Culture or Data Strategy Seek opportunities to increase stakeholder ability to use data Help to plan for and lead the training of school and regional staff on using data systems and interpreting data reports Assist with mentoring school and organizational leaders on using data to improve instructional planning and drive student achievement Serve as expert and contributing member of cross-functional teams on topics such as: Who we are … We are known as Merck & Co., Inc., Rahway, New Jersey, USA in the United States and Canada and MSD everywhere else. Today, our company continues to be at the forefront of research to deliver innovative health solutions and advance the prevention and treatment of diseases that threaten people and animals around the world. Summary/Objective The Data Governance Analyst will support the data governance program to promote a common framework for design and operationalizing data governance processes, ensure common interpretation of data, business definitions, and other information assets across multiple business units within American University. The incumbent will: Collaborate with campus partners and Office of Information Technology colleagues on the establishment, ongoing work and analysis related to American University’s Data Governance Program. Ensure successful delivery of the data governance framework solution by engaging in communication, planning, project management, scope prioritization, risk management, change management, testing, and validation activities with both campus business partners and OIT technical teams. Essential Functions        Collaborates extensively with the Analytics and Data Services team, product managers and development teams on projects and initiatives with data implications and impacts.              Leads design, development, and maintenance of the AU Data Governance Center (Collibra) - a repository which will facilitate and enable shared understandings of data definitions and foster trust in university data assets.              Serves as co-chair for the Application & Data Stewards Working Group, facilitates discussions to recommend and documents standard definitions and formats; disseminates data standards to business users and technical personnel; and promotes the creation and use of data management best practices within the business and technical community.              Works with Analytics and Data Services team, Office of Institutional Research and Assessment and Office of the Registrar on data governance program deliverables and projects.              Develops integrations between Data Management tools including but not limited to workflow engineering, setting up scripts, calling (web) service APIs, adding a Java module, creating integration with a target systems, developing scripts to import and export data.              Performs data research and analysis by working with the business subject matter experts to understand business processes, querying source data, identifying relationships between source data elements, and identifying business context of the data elements.              Identifies data management metrics, and designs data quality scorecards.              Develops and maintain supporting documentation. Identifies and implements improvement opportunities.              Enhances professional knowledge and skills by attending conferences and advanced training in required areas of expertise.       Work Environment Availability after-hours to support staff as needed. Required Education and Experience        Bachelor's degree or equivalent              5-8 years of relevant experience              Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, and the ability to interact and collaborate and work effectively with all levels of management, business customers and OIT teams.              Experience in data analysis, data quality, data warehousing and/or data enrichment.              Ability to take initiative and work independently, given a problem statement and a general guidance.              Excellent analytical skills and requirement discovery experience.       Preferred Education and Experience        Working experience in a Higher Education domain.              Hands-on experience in Collibra Administration – Managing workflows, Data Catalog Integration and care and feeding of environment.              Experience in implementing and supporting data governance solutions at large and medium sized organizations across multiple business domains.              Excellent understanding of best practices in data governance, data management principles and ability to perform independent data analysis.              Experience with enterprise data systems (ERP, CRM, Data Warehousing).              Strong SQL skills: proficient writing advanced queries to solve complex questions. Experience with JavaScript development; REST API and web services; programming skills to write Python or R scripts.              Demonstrated technical aptitude and the ability to work with different business areas and new systems/technologies. Overview:     Canvas Worldwide. Named “Most Innovative Agency” by Campaign US, is an independent media agency that provides ingenious solutions for brands looking to challenge the status quo.   The Analyst, Social Media is an entry level position where both Account and Media responsibilities will be learned on the job. The Analyst will assist the larger team to execute paid media tactics, optimize campaigns, track budget pacing, pull data and extrapolate insights, and make recommendations based on in-market results. Digital media is a 24 hour, 7-day a week medium so the work is fast-paced and sometimes ad hoc. The ability to work as part of a team in such an environment is critical, as is a sense of innate curiosity, attention to detail and a self-motivated work ethic.  In the Analyst role, you will focus on Paid Social Media as you work toward completion of a predetermined checklist to determine your mastery of the fundamentals in this channel. You will learn the ins and out of buying advertising on Facebook, Instagram, Twitter, Snap and TikTok. You will get to understand how to reach a brand’s target audience, what ad units to leverage when, how to activate media and analyze campaign performance.  Responsibilities:  Handle set-up of our paid social media campaigns including setting up campaigns, ads, and audience parameters. You will support your peers by reviewing their work to ensure correct set-up and to avoid errors. Monitor campaigns for traffic abnormalities and to ensure proper budget pacing to avoid under- or over-spend. Participate in campaign success by identifying opportunities for performance improvements and implementing optimizations. You will learn how to analyze data. Data let’s us know what is working or not working in our social media efforts. This includes running reports for internal purposes as well as client requests. Every advertising campaign requires financial commitment from our clients. It is your responsibility to set-up all campaign budget parameters into our billing tool called Prisma. Each month you will verify the previous month’s platform spend matches the invoices we receive from our social media vendors. You will meet with our social vendors regularly and you will be tasked with keeping abreast of the latest advertising news. This will help you and your team stay on top of the latest trends in tools and technology Qualifications:  Bachelor's Degree 0-1 years of experience preferably in a media/PR agency Proven ability to drive projects from start to finish Excellent written and verbal communication skills Strong organizational and analytical skills Excellent time management skills and ability to follow through Extremely detail-oriented Possess a strong and proven ability to prioritize and handle multiple tasks with flexibility and communicate priorities to Supervisor High level proficiency and knowledge of Microsoft Office products as well as planning tools Salary and Benefits   Competitive salary. Generous benefits including health coverage, unlimited PTO and matching 401(k)  Canvas Worldwide is an Equal Opportunity Employer All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex including sexual orientation and gender identity, national origin, disability, protected Veteran Status, or any other characteristic protected by applicable federal, state, or local law.

Job Description:    Horizon Media is seeking a Senior Analyst of Data Analytics who will be an outstanding addition to the CBS Broadcast, Paramount+ and Showtime team. The right person for this role thrives in a fast-paced environment, can navigate new data sets with ease, loves problem-solving and is a good communicator. If you are someone who gains personal happiness from transforming data into knowledge for business insights, then this is a phenomenal role for you.   You will design innovative analytic approaches across linear, digital campaign, and client data to showcase meaningful business insights and strategic recommendations for future business decisions. In addition to the technical aspects required, it will involve cultivating and maintaining effective working relationships with a variety of Agency groups.    We are looking for someone who is intellectually curious with the drive and experience to identify, frame and solve business problems. They must be a critical thinker who can provide creative strategic solutions and who can follow-through with flawless execution by working closely with other technical data teams to learn technical processes that may be unfamiliar to them. Critical to the role is the ability to provide thought leadership that can drive our capabilities through analytic innovations.  Responsibilities :  Build analysis, data visualizations, and multi-functional reporting that provides insights to the media team and clients Advance the analytical capabilities of the business, collaborate in the design of diagnostic solutions, and deliver outstanding data insights Use internal and external analytics and data visualization tools, SQL, and scripting languages to access and analyze multivariate data Provide analytics expertise to key business partners regarding data & analytics questions, communicating insights to domain experts and executives alike Understanding client and planning team needs & questions to better utilize the Inscape data in developing actionable insights Determine what kinds of classifications and level of granularity is needed to answer key business questions/concerns Ability to generate clear, concise, and comprehensive analyses that tell the story behind the data! Business acumen – understands the strategic levers of the content streaming and broadcast businesses and how analytics is a catalyst for decision making. Demonstrated ability to be creative; to put structure around vague and unstructured requests/discussions. Persistence: Demonstrate tenacity and willingness to go the distance to get new things done. Master the ins and outs of Inscape’s ACR technology and TV viewing dataset to identify viewing trends, consumers’ interests and content categories that will help us drive growth for our clients’ entertainment properties. Responsible for defining, refining, and evolving the methodology in which the Inscape data is extracted to address client needs & updating query rules as needed Provide insights and recommendations based on the data – should help clients understand how campaigns performed, but also the implications for future planning Be up to date on how Inscape changes or evolves their methodology of tracking and providing the data Understand how Inscape lives in the larger ecosystem of Horizon tools’ including Horizon’s integrated data platform, Blu Qualifications :  4+ years of experience as an analyst in a data and analytics domain with excellent SQL, Python, or R skills for complex querying, advanced analysis, performance optimization, and working with data at scale Extensive experience writing advance SQL statements Advance the analytical capabilities of the business, collaborate in the design of diagnostic solutions, and deliver outstanding data insights and products Experience in Snowflake, Redshift, Azure, or other major cloud computing platforms for bid data processing Ability to build strong working relationships with teammates, business partners, and technical colleagues Skill sets required:    SQL KNIME – preferable but not required Alteryx Tableau Snowflake Linear TV proficiency and understanding of ratings methodology Deep digital platform and SDK analytics experience (preferably with Kochava) Experience working with and querying/combining large data sets on a transactional level Experience working with CDP’s/DMPs / identity & device graphs Experience working on tune in, theatrical and/or entertainment brands preferred Experience defining and documenting agency channel measurement methodologies in a research/scientific level of detail

And the visionaries whose new technologies could transform the way people live and work.    They come to SVB for our expertise, deep network and nearly forty years of experience in the industries we serve, and to partner with diverse teams of passionate, enterprising SVBers, dedicated to an inclusive approach to helping them grow and succeed at every stage of their business. We pride ourselves in having both a diverse client roster and an equally diverse and inclusive organization. Job Description    Business Data Analyst I, Startup Banking    Job Description    As the market leader in providing financial services and expertise to the world’s most innovative tech and life science companies and investors, SVB possesses what is arguably the most valuable dataset in the startup and venture capital ecosystem. Through the Analytics and Sales Operations team, we place a strong emphasis on being a data-driven organization by empowering our sales teams across each of our major business units with this powerful dataset. In addition to our emphasis on data, the ASO team ensures SVB’s complex and ever-evolving business runs smoothly through technology, training, and enablement. Our team members are analytical and strategic, with a pragmatic sense of how to get things done.    This Business Data Analyst position will sit within the Sales Operations team, whose mission is to enhance the success of the market facing team by empowering their decision making with data, analytics, and insights. This position offers the opportunity to work on a collaborative and cross-functional team and to support ~30 sales and relationship managers within our Startup Banking (early-stage companies) practice.    Primary Responsibilities:  Researching and profiling prospects Managing leads from specific channels Identifying opportunities within specific channels to increase market share Preparing regularly occurring reports on business and industry performance to track strategic objectives Training sales teams on CRM and Business Intelligence tools to drive analysis of sales and activities Supporting client meetings and events by preparing sales teams with appropriate research on company financials, market trends, etc. Collaborating with sales, sales technology, and sales training & enablement teams to document, communicate, and enforce policies and processes Automating and improving scalable processes, tools, and dashboards to drive operational and business efficiency Assisting with maintenance and accuracy of company data within SVB’s data warehouse, CRM system and other repositories Assisting with ad hoc business analytics requests to empower sales relationship managers Qualifications:  1-2 years of experience with a focus on data and analytics Bachelor’s degree in a quantitative discipline (e.g., Economics, Mathematics, Statistics) Aptitude for framing business questions in analytic terms and translating business requirements into useful datasets and analyses with actionable insights Experience using and developing reports, metrics, and dashboards with data analytics, data visualization, and presentation tools (e.g., Excel, PowerPoint, SQL, Tableau) Client service oriented and able to partner with individuals at all levels Effective, clear, and concise communication skills, verbal and written Some experience within the innovation economy is preferred   © 2021 SVB Financial Group. At ALLO, we believe people are our biggest asset. Our team brings the ALLO mission to life because as local members of each community, we live, work, play, and volunteer right here with you. We're passionate about being involved and contributing to the success and progress of each of our fiberhoods.    We pursue these passions because ALLO leaders have created a workplace where folks are valued, ideas are heard, and work-life balance is an everyday practice.  Fact: ALLO knows how to build. Since 2003, we’ve built the fiber optic network completely from scratch for seven of our fiberhoods. Since our pioneering days in the early 2000s, we’ve built up our team too, going from about 80 employees to more than 500 and our customer base exploded symmetrically. We’ve never thought of ourselves as the little guy and now we’ve got the numbers to prove our prowess and stamina in an often disappointing industry. That’s why we’re looking for an experienced Analyst to join our team.  Do you love digging into the nitty-gritty? Are you a motivated problem solver? We might have just the GIG for you. Knowledge and experience are essential; we need someone who doesn’t have to google SQL, Oracle, Crystal, and Python before the interview. We also look for those who demonstrate a natural instinct for our core values: Honest, Local, Exceptional, and Hassle-Free. Advanced fiber-optic knowledge isn’t required, just a desire to learn, build and keep our future-focused business moving forward.    RESPONSIBILITIES:      Commit to Performance Based Organization (PBO) & Easy to Do Business with (ETDBW) philosophy.        Improve ALLO’s performance by providing data-driven analysis results to drive strategic decision making.        Provide strategic and defensible recommendations for improving our systems, processes, and strategies based upon findings supported by research and data analysis.        Interact with all levels of the organization to facilitate analysis requirements and reporting needs.        Analyze data for trends, correlations, and other key characteristics, and report findings.        Develop reports and dashboards to communicate performance and deliver insight to customers while monitoring data quality issues.        Continuously seek out opportunities to add value through process automation and programmatic solutions to manual tasks.        Be proactive to customer needs and support the ALLO Management team as our primary customer.        Develop and maintain knowledge of latest trends and best practices.        Effectively present and discuss analysis and insights with customers in narrative or visual form.      Colorado Residents: typical pay range for this role will be from $50,000 - $70,000 depending on experience.    EDUCATION:      4-year college degree preferred or equivalent experience needed      EXPERIENCE:      1+ years of data analytics with proven track record of experience.        Preferable to see examples or published work.      SKILLS/KNOWLEDGE/ABILITIES:      Technical skill-set        Experience with data access and structuring tool(s) (e.g. SQL, PostgreSQL, Oracle, Python)        Experience with analysis and reporting dashboard software (e.g. DbVisualizer, SAP Business Objects, Microsoft Power BI)        Experience in mining, cleaning, processing, and joining data from a variety of sources including SQL servers, AWS environments, internal systems, and flat files.        Advanced experience with Microsoft Excel, including formulas, charts and Pivot Tables        Excellent oral/written and interpersonal communication skills.        Excellent analytical and problem solving skills.        Ability to conceptualize and analyze complex business processes.        Negotiation, facilitation and presentation skills.        Ability to define and achieve business goals and deadlines while working both independently & collaboratively.        Customer-focused philosophy.        Ability to manage multiple conflicting priorities and consistently meet deadlines.        Ability to meet and manage customer expectations in a professional and timely manner.      People are our passion. At ALLO, we don’t treat you like a number. You’re a human being.   Get ready to plug into the perks at ALLO:  Free ALLO Service: We’ll pick up the tab on your ALLO fiber internet, TV, and phone bill. Seriously! Retirement Plan: The fiber future isn’t the only one we care about. We match your 401(k) savings up to 5%. Health and Wellness: Participate in quarterly wellness challenges, and we’ll deposit extra cash into your checking or health savings accounts. Benefits: Our benefits include medical, vision, and dental with low employee costs. Not to mention a generous ETO policy. Plus, if you’ve got student loan debt, we’ve got a repayment assistance program you’ll want to get in on. Sponsorships: Are you passionate about a local fundraiser or philanthropy? We strive to give back to what matters most to our communities. Tuition Assistance: Have a thirst for knowledge? We like that, which is why we’re proud to offer assistance with the cost of your tuition.   ALLO is an Equal Opportunity Employer. Overview:     The Data Analyst is responsible for data gathering, analysis, and reporting. This role will be required to translate business needs into data and analytical requirements and deliver those requirements within deadlines and at a high level of accuracy.  Responsibilities:   Principal Accountabilities & Deliverables Collects and analyzes complex data for reporting and/or performance (trend) analysis Develops and utilizes complex SQL queries and other data extraction techniques to prepare data for analysis, ensuring alignment between the data and the underlying business processes that the data reflects. Prepares a wide variety of reports and provides data and management information for internal audiences Participates in high-level business initiatives and assist with all levels of metric reporting Report Automation- work with IT to publish canned reports based on business needs/requests. Performs the analysis, explores all appropriate options and performs constant validation against existing data/reporting. Serves as data steward to validate high profile or external data to ensure accurate reporting. Other duties as assigned. Qualifications:   Knowledge, Skills, & Abilities Education / Experience  Bachelor’s Degree required in Economics, Math, Computer Science or related field 2+ years’ experience in data gathering, data organization, and analysis required   Skills  Intermediate to Advanced SQL querying skills required Advanced working knowledge of Microsoft Excel Business Objects/Business Intelligence experience preferred Strong knowledge and experience with relational database platforms, including SQL Server Excellent written and oral communication skills, especially in conveying technical concepts to non-technical audiences Comfortable working in a fast-paced environment where deadlines are essential Competent in organizing, planning, and prioritizing work Strong attention to detail to ensure accuracy and provide validation of results Strong analytical skills and ability to identify appropriate analytical approaches depending on the business need.

Bridg is a Customer Data Platform (CDP) built for brick and mortar retailers and CPG brands to identify, understand and engage unknown in-store customers. Our platform was built around a single premise: level the data playing field for brick and mortar retail businesses. Put simply, we help our clients solve the anonymous in-store customer challenge. We unify offline and online data sources, resolve identities, enrich profiles with robust second and third party data and power targeted, personalized advertising across virtually any channel.      The end result?      A single 360º consumer view. Hundreds of shopper insights. And endless analytics and marketing opportunities.      Bridg is looking for a Data Analyst to join the new Data & Analytics team who will work closely with customer facing teams to assess, interpret, organize and prioritize our clients’ reporting and analytics needs and ensure successful achievement of platform use cases. Candidates should have extensive experience working with analytics and visualization tools and should be familiar with cloud data warehouse technology. Ideal candidates will be naturally curious, have good business sense and excel at synthesizing massive amounts of data into compelling arguments to enable effective decision making. In this role, you will help build data products for our clients and deliver repeatable service engagements as part of our platform to drive additional value.    Please note this role is remote and we are open to all candidates within the continental United States.Responsibilities Include Creation of standardized dashboards to be integrated into the Bridg Platform (via Sisense) for client consumption as well as to support internal stakeholders Delivery of customized dashboards in App or in clients’ visualization tool of choice (Tableau, Power BI, Looker, etc) as needed Ad hoc analysis and delivery of custom SQL queries to be used by clients as needed Ongoing analytics updates for clients highlighting key insights in consumer behavior over time Standardized campaign performance reporting (lift measurement) and ad hoc analysis to support client success as needed Work with Client Success and Data teams to solve complex client challenges using data science techniques Influence the product strategy including incorporation of data science modelsRequired Skills and Background 2+ years of professional experience in business analytics Advanced experience with SQL and knowledge of Python, and/or R programming languages, A MUST Familiarity with analytical cloud warehouse solutions (Snowflake, Redshift, BigQuery, etc) Extensive experience with advanced visualization tools creating automated solutions that leverage large scale datasets, strong dashboard presentation skills a plus! Working knowledge of Sisense a plus. Bachelor’s degree highly preferred. Degrees in quantitative areas (Stats, Math, CS, etc.) a plus Consistent track record of high performance and effective collaboration within complex organizations Experience and desire for working in a start-up environment, contributing to developing business infrastructure and aggressively scaling a high growth business Able to operate at an enterprise level, using creative and innovative solutions with a relentless focus on customer experience. Exceptional written and verbal communication skills – extraordinary listening skills.About Bridg:    Bridg is a marketing software company that provides a CRM solution, email and SMS marketing, insights and analytics, mobile app and loyalty program development for restaurants and retailers. Powered by transaction data, Bridg builds unique 360º customer profiles to understand individualized behavior patterns, providing clients with deep data science used to create wide-reaching, effective personalized marketing campaigns that drive traffic and sales in a measurable way.   Our headquarters is located in West LA / Santa Monica, and we offer competitive salaries, great benefits, and a high-energy environment with lots of room for personal and professional growth.

bring structure where there is ambiguity Anticipate and resolve stakeholder resistance and other risks, in order to bring others along to a desired outcome Develop a trusted client partnership by listening to unspoken concerns and seeking to understand the client’s business and environment as a whole Grow with Propeller by supporting internal initiatives to uplift our people, processes, and market presence Cultivate new skillsets based on your own professional development goals utilizing the learning and development budget provided by Propeller Work where you live; all our consultants work locally with no travel required You have: 4-12 years of experience in Business Intelligence or Information Management, preferably within a consulting environment Demonstrated ability to create and drive roadmaps for analytics projects and to develop an organizational data strategy Working knowledge of programming languages (SQL, Python, R, etc.) Experience using various data analysis and visualization tools to uncover and present relevant insights, including visualization/reporting tools (such as Tableau, PowerBI, Spotfire, Qlikview) or visualization libraries (such as R, ggplot2, Python matplotlib/seaborn/bokeh, Javascript D3) Experience applying statistical principles and knowledge of relational and dimensional database structures, theories, principles, and practice Experience with various delivery methodologies in technology environments; We do that by offering a competitive salary, uncapped bonus eligibility, an employee stock ownership program and many other benefits. Location:    Propeller employees are working in a hybrid environment with the flexibility to work from home, their local Propeller office, or their client site as needed. Responsible for creating and maintaining the data within the Kinder Morgan Pipeline Open Data Standard (KM PODS) Esri Geodatabase. The accuracy and integrity of the KM PODS geodatabase is upheld via adding new data, maintaining existing data, running daily quality checks, following KM PODS business process workflows, and working from the KM PODS procedures and technical guides. This role may work directly with, but not limited to, the following groups within Kinder Morgan: Compliance Systems, Risk Engineering, Drafting, Codes and Standards, ILI Integrity, Construction Project Management, and Field Operations. The PODS Natural Gas Pipeline Data Analyst responsibilities include, but not limited to, of the following: Utilize data maintenance / as-builting applications to review, edit and approve data within a versioned ESRI geodatabase. Work from multiple electronic and hard copy engineering, field survey, inspection, and other approved source documents for as-built data capture. Overview:     Canvas Worldwide. Named “Most Innovative Agency” by Campaign US, is an independent media agency that provides ingenious solutions for brands looking to challenge the status quo.   The Analyst, Social Media is an entry level position where both Account and Media responsibilities will be learned on the job. The Analyst will assist the larger team to execute paid media tactics, optimize campaigns, track budget pacing, pull data and extrapolate insights, and make recommendations based on in-market results. Digital media is a 24 hour, 7-day a week medium so the work is fast-paced and sometimes ad hoc. The ability to work as part of a team in such an environment is critical, as is a sense of innate curiosity, attention to detail and a self-motivated work ethic.  In the Analyst role, you will focus on Paid Social Media as you work toward completion of a predetermined checklist to determine your mastery of the fundamentals in this channel. You will learn the ins and out of buying advertising on Facebook, Instagram, Twitter, Snap and TikTok. You will get to understand how to reach a brand’s target audience, what ad units to leverage when, how to activate media and analyze campaign performance.  Responsibilities:  Handle set-up of our paid social media campaigns including setting up campaigns, ads, and audience parameters. You will support your peers by reviewing their work to ensure correct set-up and to avoid errors. Monitor campaigns for traffic abnormalities and to ensure proper budget pacing to avoid under- or over-spend. Participate in campaign success by identifying opportunities for performance improvements and implementing optimizations. You will learn how to analyze data. Data let’s us know what is working or not working in our social media efforts. This includes running reports for internal purposes as well as client requests. Every advertising campaign requires financial commitment from our clients. It is your responsibility to set-up all campaign budget parameters into our billing tool called Prisma. Each month you will verify the previous month’s platform spend matches the invoices we receive from our social media vendors. You will meet with our social vendors regularly and you will be tasked with keeping abreast of the latest advertising news. This will help you and your team stay on top of the latest trends in tools and technology Qualifications:  Bachelor's Degree 0-1 years of experience preferably in a media/PR agency Proven ability to drive projects from start to finish Excellent written and verbal communication skills Strong organizational and analytical skills Excellent time management skills and ability to follow through Extremely detail-oriented Possess a strong and proven ability to prioritize and handle multiple tasks with flexibility and communicate priorities to Supervisor High level proficiency and knowledge of Microsoft Office products as well as planning tools Salary and Benefits   Competitive salary. Demonstrated ability to be a positive team player across diverse internal and external organizations   Excellent skills with at least one business intelligence or data visualization software tool such as PowerBI, Tableau, Qlikview, SAP, R, etc. Programming experience (SQL, R, Python, M, etc.) preferable.   Ability to travel 10%   Education Required: Bachelor's Degree   Education Preferred: Bachelor's Degree   Experience Required: 3 years   Experience Preferred: 3 years    About JAX:    The Jackson Laboratory (JAX) is an independent, nonprofit biomedical research institution with more than 2,400 employees. Headquartered in Bar Harbor, Maine, it has a National Cancer Institute-designated Cancer Center in Augusta, Maine, a genomic medicine institute in Farmington, Connecticut, and facilities in Ellsworth, Maine, Sacramento, California, and Shanghai, China. Its mission is to discover precise genomic solutions for disease and empower the global biomedical community in the shared quest to improve human health.    JAX employees work in a collaborative, value-driven, and team-based environment where the focus is on advancing science and improving patients’ lives. Researchers apply genetics to increase the understanding of human disease and advance treatments and cures for cancer, neurological and immune disorders, diabetes, aging, and heart disease. JAX was voted among the top 15 “Best Places to Work in Academia” in the United States in a poll conducted by The Scientist magazine!    EEO Statement:  The Jackson Laboratory provides equal employment opportunities to all employees and applicants for employment in all job classifications without regard to race, color, religion, age, mental disability, physical disability, medical condition, gender, sexual orientation, genetic information, ancestry, marital status, national origin, veteran status, and other classifications protected by applicable state and local non-discrimination laws.

to enhance the department's effectiveness and decision-making Establishes and maintains a monitoring and reporting system that regularly communicates performance improvements and innovation efforts and impacts across the department Identifies unit costs and conducts cost-benefit analyses on programs and services, emphasizing and promoting returns on investments and the quantitative determination for the unmet need of services Monitors and responds to public and client requests and questions submitted via the Client Portal the HSD website or HSD leadership Collaborates with divisional leadership ensuring program data (including analysis, if necessary) is available and comprehensible for use in program planning, decision making, and evaluation Leads and coordinates department committees involving technology, data, or communication Interfaces and coordinates with other County departments to implement key department initiatives Assists Data Integrity and Analytics Manager with special projects and reports Working Conditions The position is based in an office environment and may require travel to and from various locations throughout the County during a scheduled workday, subject to County policies regarding the use of County or private vehicles used on County business.  Selection ProcedureThe Maricopa County Human Resources Department reserves the right to admit to the selection process only those candidates considered to be the most highly qualified. Those selected will be assessed based on the evaluation of listed education and experience. The hiring authority will interview and select the successful candidate from a list provided by Human Resources.  All offers of employment made to new hires and rehires at Maricopa County are contingent upon successful completion of a post-offer, pre-employment thorough background investigation. A background investigation is conducted on a current employee who changes to a Safety Sensitive Position or one having the potential for serious adverse impact on the integrity or efficiency of the County. These requirements do not pertain to employees of elected officials who undergo background investigation processes administered through their respective offices.  Maricopa County is an EEO/ADA Reasonable Accommodation Employer. Attention Current Maricopa County Employees: As of 1/1/2022, the Judicial Branch of Arizona in Maricopa County will formalize themselves as a separate entity and employer from Maricopa County. To learn more about how that may affect you, please click here.Maricopa County offers a Total Compensation Package that includes competitive salaries and a comprehensive, affordable benefits package. High value is placed on employee well-being and meeting the needs of our employees and their families. Our benefits package is comprised of traditional benefits like medical, prescription, dental, vision, and other health benefits. Employees are supported by various wellness programs including classes, coaching, and fitness center opportunities. Our generous benefit options are some of the best in Arizona and just one of the unique advantages of working for Maricopa County. Below is a representative listing of typical benefits received by most full-time employees.  Holidays and Leave Maricopa County observes ten paid holidays per year. Most County employees accrue vacation (starting at three weeks per year for full-time employees) and sick leave (starting at one hour for every 30 hours worked for all employees). Employees also receive paid leave for other needs such as jury duty, civic duty, and bereavement.   Medical, Prescription, Behavioral Health, Dental, Vision, and Flexible Spending Accounts We understand how important health care is to maintaining a good quality of life. We also know our employees want to have the freedom to choose benefit plans to best meet their needs. Eligible employees may choose from four medical plan options, an HMO, PPO, and two HDHP (High Deductible Health Plans) with a health savings account. When employees enroll in medical coverage, they are automatically enrolled in prescription and behavioral health coverage as well. There are three dental plans from which to choose, two PPO plans and a pre-paid dental plan that functions like an HMO. As is the case with medical, the plans range in cost, flexibility, and network of providers. The vision plan provides employees and their covered dependents access to routine vision services and materials, including an annual eye exam. For those who wish to set aside pre-tax dollars to pay for eligible healthcare and dependent care expenses, the flexible spending accounts are suitable for that need.  Life and Disability Insurance  Because life sometimes takes unexpected turns, the County offers life insurance coverage to help employees and their loved ones in the event of death. Basic life and basic accidental death & dismemberment insurance equivalent to one times an employee's annual base salary is provided at no cost, with the option for employees to purchase additional coverage including spouse and child life insurance. Disability insurance is available to replace a portion of an employee's salary should they experience a short-term illness or injury.  Retirement  Eligible employees are covered by one of several State-sponsored retirement pension plans, including the Arizona State Retirement System (ASRS) and the Public Safety Personnel Retirement System (PSPRS). Additionally, there's the option to contribute to a 457(b) Savings Plan that provides employees with a variety of investment opportunities. For those employees who retire from the County and from their retirement system, and have accrued 1,000 or more hours of sick leave, the County makes a $10,000 contribution to a Post-Employment Health Plan set up on their behalf to be used for payment of eligible out-of-pocket healthcare expenses.  Group Legal Plan Maricopa County offers employees group discounts to purchase coverage for legal services such as adoptions, family matters, wills and trusts.  Wellness Maricopa County's Wellness Works program promotes health and wellness for employees and their families by focusing on physical activity, good nutrition, self-care and stress management. Maricopa County offers eligible employees a wellness incentive for completing required activities. By meeting a set of criteria, employees and their families can get reimbursed for participating in a Weight Watchers Program. On-site fitness facilities and fitness classes are provided to employees at various locations around the County. Employees and their families also have the opportunity to receive a discounted fitness club membership at LA Fitness. Employees have access to smoking cessation programs and health-related classes on various topics including nutrition, exercise and stress management. Employees located downtown benefit from an onsite pharmacy and clinic. Every fall, flu vaccines are offered to employees at various County locations.   Employee Assistance Program (EAP) When employees and their families are faced with personal issues, confidential, short-term counseling and referral services are available to them at no cost.   Employee Discounts Maricopa County subscribes to a service association which provides employees with volume discounts for sporting events, entertainment, and many other services.  Commute Options Program (COP)  Maricopa County provides free Valley Metro passes for the bus and light rail systems for commuting to/from work; a vanpool subsidy is also provided. Employees can decrease stress, decrease wear and tear on their vehicle and help the environment all at the same time.  New Employee Orientation (NEO)  NEO provides new employees with information about Maricopa County such as: history, organizational structure, Merit Rules, County policies and procedures, County pay system and benefits and employee programs.  Rewarding Ideas/Employee Suggestions  Employees are provided with incentives to generate ideas for improvements that result in cost reduction through increased efficiency and productivity, improved processes and procedures and elimination of duplication and waste. Our employees' ideas could put money in their pocket!!  Tuition Reimbursement To promote Maricopa County's long term employee retention objectives, our employees are eligible to receive financial assistance to continue their education, help make them more productive, enhance their job performance, and equip them to pursue new opportunities within County government.  To learn more about the County's generous benefits, visit the Maricopa County Employee Benefits and Wellness website.Agency    Maricopa County   Address301 W Jefferson 8th Floor  Phoenix, Arizona, 85003 Phone602-506-3755

All roles at JumpCloud are Remote unless otherwise specified in the Job Description. About JumpCloud    JumpCloud’s mission is to Make Work Happen®, providing simple, secure access to corporate technology resources from any device, or any location. The JumpCloud Directory Platform gives IT, security operations, and DevOps a single, cloud-based solution to control and manage employee identities, their devices, and apply conditional access controls based on Zero Trust principals. Since launching in 2012, our global user base has grown to more than 150,000 organizations, with more than 5,000 paying customers including Cars.com, GoFundMe, Grab, ClassPass, Uplight and Peloton. JumpCloud has raised over $400M from world-class investors including Sapphire Ventures, General Atlantic, Sands Capital, Atlassian, and CrowdStrike. Our teams are growing fast, too, and we're looking for talent across engineering, sales, customer success, marketing, product management, and more. Join our team of dedicated, passionate, and creative people who are eager to change the IT industry forever.      We’re looking for a Senior Analyst, Data Curation to support JumpCloud’s Enterprise Data and Analytics team in developing and refining a data model that supports JumpCloud’s growth strategy. A successful analyst will exhibit an entrepreneurial spirit and enjoy tackling data management problems that most other people cannot solve, as well as shaping the future capabilities of JumpCloud’s performance reporting and data governance. Come be a part of an exciting new team where you will be able to work on challenging projects, rich data sets, and develop valuable skills. This role involves frequent engagement with analytics partners and data engineering to mature our data model and pipeline and will report to the senior manager of data.  What you’ll be doing: Act as a trust liaison between the business and data engineering; help to prioritize and streamline data ingestion efforts. Tackle key data curation and governance efforts to optimize the data model for quality, reliability, and self-service capabilities Assess the current state of our data model and make recommendations on developing a scalable and sustainable solution Identify, design, and implement internal process improvements: Automating manual processes, optimizing data delivery, evaluating our infrastructure for greater scalability, etc. Build processes supporting data transformation, data structures, metadata, dependency and workload management. Work with stakeholders including the Product, Growth, Marketing, Finance, Customer Success, and Sales teams to assist with data-related technical issues and support their data infrastructure needs. Partner with analytics and operational experts to develop data systems that provide actionable insights into customer acquisition, operational efficiency, and other key business performance metrics. Assist in developing documentation around system integration, data flows, data dictionary, user guides and best practices.We’re looking for: Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Statistics, Informatics, Information Systems or another quantitative field Advanced working knowledge and experience in SQL and relational databases; Snowflake is preferable Experience with object-oriented/object function scripting languages; Python and/or Scala is preferable Experience with data pipeline and workflow management tools is a plus. Prior experience with AWS Glue, Lambda, dbt, Airflow or similar tools is preferable Familiarity with data design, dimensional modeling principles and data integration concepts Demonstrate understanding and application of effective change management and version control techniques. Git/Gitlab/Github experience highly preferred Experience developing data quality and validation checks, as well as addressing service incidents related to data load or quality issues, ensuring data delivery SLAs are met as expected Solid understanding of Salesforce data architecture and best practices; Fivetran experience is a plus Solid project management and organizational skills; Agile experience is a plus Experience performing root cause analysis on internal and external data and processes to answer specific business questions and identify opportunities for improvement Experience supporting and working with cross-functional teams in a fast-paced, dynamic environment; Start-up experience is preferable Experience with product-led-growth (PLG) is a plus   In accordance with the Colorado Equal Pay for Equal Work Act, the approximate annual compensation range for this role, depending on individual candidate level and experience, is $100,000-$130,000, including base salary and any related bonuses or commissions.   JumpCloud provides a comprehensive benefits package, with several medical plans to choose from including a high deductible HSA plan with employer contribution, two dental plans, vision insurance, flexible spending account (FSA), employee assistance program (EAP), short- and long-term disability, life insurance and a 401k savings plan with match. We have an unlimited vacation policy.   Where you’ll be working/Location:    JumpCloud is committed to being Remote First, meaning that are you able to work remotely within the country noted in the Job Description.      For US Roles: All roles posted in United States locations do require that you be located within one of the 50 U.S. States. Our Headquarters is in the Denver/Boulder, CO area but as a remote company, you are able to work remotely anywhere in the U.S. If you would like to spend time in the office in Denver/Boulder area, you are welcome do that as well.   Why JumpCloud?    If you thrive working in a fast, SaaS-based environment and you are passionate about solving challenging technical problems, we look forward to hearing from you! JumpCloud is an incredible place to share and grow your expertise! You’ll work with amazing talent across each department who are passionate about our mission. We’re out of the box thinkers, so your unique ideas and approaches for conceiving a product and/or feature will be welcome. You’ll have a voice in the organization as you work with a seasoned executive team, a supportive board and in a proven market that our customers are excited about.   One of JumpCloud's three core values is to “Build Connections.” To us that means creating " human connection with each other regardless of our backgrounds, orientations, geographies, religions, languages, gender, race, etc. We care deeply about the people that we work with and want to see everyone succeed." - Rajat Bhargava, CEO   Please submit your résumé and brief explanation about yourself and why you would be a good fit for JumpCloud. Please note JumpCloud is not accepting third party resumes at this time.   JumpCloud is an equal opportunity employer. All applicants will be considered for employment without attention to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, veteran or disability status.   #LI-Remote #BI-Remote

MoneyGeek is a U.S. based personal finance website with the mission to help people make smarter financial decisions. We offer great pay and great benefits. Come join our team!  We are seeking a full-time employee who can help us research and collect new datasets via hand collection, scraping, or other methods.  The ideal candidate can analyze and make recommendations or draw conclusions from those datasets. It is a benefit to have existing expertise on U.S. insurance products, but this position does not require it.  Once hired, you will be required to learn and understand products in order to collect appropriate data.  Data collection may be both quantitative (for example, insurance quotes) or qualitative (for example, coverages and benefits offered by insurance companies).  The interview process will consist of one video interview and a small skills assessment assignment.  Are you ready to join the MoneyGeek team? Expectations  Approx 40 hours per week  Fast learner who is curious to learn about U.S. insurance products  Able to collect new datasets in an efficient and creative way  Able to analyze new datasets to pull out relevant metrics for our users (averages, ranges, availability, etc.)  Willing to learn and improve processes over time  Willing to learn Slack and Asana communication tools  Minimum Qualifications  Can speak in 100% clear, fluent English  Experience collecting and analyzing datasets  Project management experience  Personal finance topical knowledge is a plus  Familiar with Google Workplace tools (docs, sheets, etc)

Position Details    Position Information    Classification Title       MnSCU Academic Professional 2      Working Title       Academic Research Analyst      Hire Types       Staff      Division       Century College      Department       Finance/Administration      Unit       Institutional Effectiveness & Planning      Location       White Bear Lake, MN      FLSA       Non-Exempt      Full/Part Time       Full Time      FTE       1.0      Employment Condition       Unlimited       Work Shift       Days      Work Schedule/Hours/DaysHours:Monday – Friday 8:00am – 4:30pm      Posting DetailsCurrent Salary Range:         $22.38 – $32.49/hour – $46,729 – $67,839 Annually       Salary Range Effective 7/01/2022:$22.94 – $33.30/hour – $47,899 – $69,530 AnnuallySalary Minimum       $46,729      Salary Maximum       $67,839      Salary Type       Annual      Bargaining Unit/Plan       214, MAPE      Job DescriptionPosition Purpose & Responsibilities:         This position serves Century College’s Office of Institutional Effectiveness by engaging in research to support data-informed decision-making.                Under general supervision, gather, create, and analyze data using descriptive statistical techniques that result in the generation of reports appropriate to a variety of internal and external stakeholders. Responsibilities include leading efforts on the update, maintenance, and improvement of standing internal reports and external reporting as well as:        Coordinate, oversee, and update standing internal reports for units of the College to support administrative decision making and operational processes.Design, analyze, and create ad hoc reports for units of the College to support administrative decision making and operational processes.Assist in the design, conversion, and/or creation of data visualization/automation for use by internal stakeholders of the institution to promote a data driven culture.Coordinate and oversee a set of standing external data reports.Coordinate and oversee institutional data integrity check processes.Required QualificationsMinimum Qualifications: (        expected to have to enter job)Bachelor’s degree in social science, computer science, statistics, or related field (or combination of relevant work experience and college education).Experience in collecting, organizing, analyzing, and summarizing data.Experience in descriptive statistics.Ability to plan and implement research projects, which rely on the use of a relational database system and data warehouses.Ability to work with complex data sets; maintain data quality and engage in validation.Proven ability to handle multiple tasks and meet deadlines; ability to prioritize and follow through on projects. Ability to react to changing situations and adapt to change in work demands, priorities, and procedures.Ability to work both independently and collaboratively.Exercise sound judgment, tact, and discretion.Proficiency with relational database management (Veera, Access, R/R Studio, etc.), word processing, and spreadsheet software.Knowledge and experience in the use of data visualization and statistical analysis software.Preferred QualificationsPreferred Qualifications:(desired but not expected to have to enter job)Extensive experience using Rapid Insight Veera Construct or Microsoft Access. Experience using Microsoft PowerBI.Experience with Python for data analysis.Experience working with Minnesota State higher education data.Experience in an institutional research office.Other RequirementsAdditional Requirements:         To facilitate proper crediting, please ensure that your resume clearly describes your experience in areas listed and indicates the beginning and ending month and year for each job held.                This position requires successful completion of employment references and a driver’s license background check.       About        Century College is a two-year community and technical college located in White Bear Lake, Minnesota. As one of the largest and most diverse and affordable colleges in Minnesota, we serve nearly 16,400 credit and non-credit students each year.                Century College offers over 150 degrees, diplomas and certificates in a wide variety of high-demand program areas, including applied design, arts and humanities, business, health sciences, human services, science, technology, engineering and mathematics (STEM), social and behavioral sciences, trade and industry, and non-credit workforce training.
